    <title><literal>Zapateller()</literal></title>

    <indexterm significance="preferred">
      <primary>Dialplan Applications</primary>

      <secondary><code>Zapateller()</code></secondary>
    </indexterm>

    <simpara>Generates the "Special Information Tone" to block advance dialing
    telemarketing systems.</simpara>

    <synopsis><command>Zapateller(<replaceable>options</replaceable>)</command></synopsis>

    <simpara>Generates the "Special Information Tone" to indicate the number
    is not valid or reachable. Some predictive dialing systems will
    automatically delete a number from the calling list if they receive this
    tone.</simpara>

    <para>The following "|"-delimited options are accepted:<variablelist
        termlength="12">
        <varlistentry>
          <term><code>answer</code></term>

          <listitem>
            <simpara>Answers the line before playing the tone
            sequence.</simpara>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term><code>nocallerid</code></term>

          <listitem>
            <simpara>Plays the tone only if no caller ID information is
            received.</simpara>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist></para>

    <programlisting>[incoming]
; Play the SIT sequence if no caller ID is present:
exten =&gt; s,1,Zapateller(nocallerid)
exten =&gt; s,n,Wait(3)
exten =&gt; s,n,Answer()</programlisting>

